                                           rdfs:subClassOf :EMMO_feb03a8a_bbb6_4918_a891_46713ef557f4 ;
                                           skos:prefLabel "SICoherentUnit"@en ;
                                           :OWLRL2DLAxioms "disjointUnionOf: SICoherentDerivedUnit, SIBaseUnit, SISpecialUnit" ;
                                           :elucidation "A unit that can be expressed as a product of powers of SI base units with no pre-factor or offset."@en ;
                                           :note "Derived units are defined as products of powers of the base units. When the numerical factor of this product is one, the derived units are called coherent derived units. The base and coherent derived units of the SI form a coherent set, designated the set of coherent SI units."@en .


